# Orghi Project Context

## Project Overview

- **Original project**: HKUDS/nanobot
- **Fork**: jjfantini/orghi
- **Goal**: Small personal assistant for personal workflows; base for submitting PRs to the open-source project. The agent is called "orghi" (internally still nanobot).

## Branch Strategy

Three main branch heads:

| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `upstream/main` | Upstream repo; target for PRs |
| `origin/main` | Kept in sync with upstream/main for development; allows the ability for the user to cleanlybranch off here to add features from the core codebase if they dont want to devleop on top of their custom orghi-main changes|
| `origin/orghi-main` | Custom code for personal needs when PRs are not merged. |

## Flow

```
upstream/main --> origin/main --> origin/orghi-main
```

Always flow upstream/main into origin/main, then into origin/orghi-main to keep the latest open-source contributions. We have a sync-upstream skill that does this for us.

## Why origin/main Exists

- Avoid merge conflicts
- Test that features do not break anything before merging into orghi-main
- Easier merge conflict resolution

## Deployment

- `orghi-main` has a deployment action that deploys orghi (nanobot) to a VPS on Digital Ocean via SSH
- Every push to `orghi-main` deploys to the droplet
- Development often happens in Cursor IDE on the remote droplet via SSH
